originalText.text:
I urge everyone to be extremely cautious with 'Strings Universal' which seems to be running a deceitful operation targeting vulnerable individuals, especially the elderly. This company, claiming to operate from Reading, UK, but apparently registered in the US, has been making scam calls. My elderly mother fell prey to their scheme, purchasing overpriced vitamins, which left her distressed and financially burdened.

It's important to note that although the caller claims to be from the UK, the calls always come from an international number. Furthermore, UK's Companies House records show that the UK branch of this company was dissolved in 2018, yet they continue to operate, possibly from the US.

Please, do not provide any personal or financial information to them and hang up immediately if you receive such a call. I also encourage reporting these incidents to both UK and US consumer protection agencies and local authorities to help prevent others from falling victim to such scams.
